回想セーブ グッドエンド
Cheers.\n< Serena >
Cheers.\n< Erika >
...\n< Serena >
...ahh.\n< Erika >

Kahahaha! So this is the taste of
victory's wine, huh?!\n< Erika >

When we fought the Minotaur, I was
rushed to the hospital and didn't even
get a sip of alcohol.\n< Erika >

To think we're celebrating that victory
now. You're as strange as ever.\n< Serena >

Serena, you've become quite the drinker
yourself. Did you learn to appreciate
the taste of alcohol in that town?\n< Erika >
Now, for another glass...\n< Erika >

Erika-sama, you're pregnant. You
shouldn't be drinking too much...\n< Serena >

Ah... right. Alcohol is bad for the kid
in my belly... wasn't it?\n< Erika >
That belly...\n< Serena >

Well, I haven't slept with any other men
around that time. It must be one of
those guys' seed that hit the mark.\n< Erika >

I was too injured for an abortion.
Before I knew it, my belly got this big.\n< Erika >

Now that it's come to this, there's
nothing to do but give birth. Even if
it's a child conceived from rape, I have
to give birth.\n< Erika >
Anyway, don't worry about me.\n< Erika >

More importantly, Serena, you've become
quite the drinker yourself. Did you
learn to appreciate the taste of alcohol
in that town?\n< Erika >

Well, I can't say I find it delicious.
But now, a little...\n< Serena >

No, actually, it still tastes strange.
It hits you right in the nose.\n< Serena >

Hahahaha. That's fine. If you start
guzzling from a young age, you'll end up
a lush like me.\n< Erika >

If I could become like Erika-sama, maybe
I should try harder to enjoy alcohol.\n< Serena >

Me? Nah, my body's all battered and
nothing's going right. There's nothing
good about aiming to be like me. Really,
really...\n< Erika >

That's not true... I respect you. Even
at this moment, my respect for you is
renewed.\n< Serena >

In Castellum, that town, I saw much
evil. A little kindness and how weak
people's hearts can be.\n< Serena >
...That's why I'm amazed now.\n< Serena >

At your demeanor, Erika-sama, your way
of conducting yourself. Your strength is
truly formidable.\n< Serena >

I wonder if I can behave like you from
now on...\n< Serena >
...\n< Erika >
You found Splendor-chan, right?\n< Erika >

Yes, she was found. It took some effort
though. While we're here, Lady Mary is
looking after her.\n< Serena >

Not a single injury, safe and sound. I'm
truly glad... truly...\n< Serena >

Then this is a grand finale. A happy
ending, huh?\n< Erika >

Well, yes. Depending on what father,
mother, and sister say...\n< Serena >

What kind of punishment they'll give me
is the only thing left to worry about.\n< Serena >
Go on and get thoroughly scolded.\n< Erika >

Man, I'm really glad. I was worried sick
in bed every day.\n< Erika >

That everything turned out okay, I'm
really glad...\n< Erika >
To the point of crying...\n< Serena >

No, see, Serena. You don't get it, you
just don't understand. Worrying about
someone means being really worried.\n< Erika >

Whether Serena is doing okay, if she's
been able to eat, if she's found a place
to stay, if she hasn't been deceived by
some bad guy, or gotten wrapped up in
something terrible...\n< Erika >

Lying in the hospital bed, those kinds
of scenes would pop into my head,
disappear, and then come back again,
each time making my chest tighten.\n< Erika >

Even I felt like this. When I think
about how your parents must feel...
Geez. Your sister must be feeling like
her heart's going to burst...\n< Erika >
Hmm...\n< Serena >

That's why you really need to go and get
scolded. It's your duty and
responsibility, Serena.\n< Erika >
Hmm...\n< Serena >

...Having a family that worries about
you is a blessing, you know. I was
raised in an orphanage and don't even
know what my mother looks like.\n< Erika >

Is that so? I recall you mentioned
before that you had run away from home,
Erika-sama.\n< Serena >

Did I say something like that? You have
a good memory.\n< Erika >

...Well, running away means I left the
orphanage. I had no intention of
becoming a nun, that's for sure.\n< Erika >

Come to think of it, at first, I did
intend to look for my mother. But the
only clue I had was her hair color.\n< Erika >
Which means?\n< Serena >

You're really latching onto this, huh?
Fine by me.\n< Erika >

Well, when my mother left me at the
orphanage, right? It seems she gave me a
charm to hold onto.\n< Erika >

It was woven into my hair. I figure it's
probably my mother's hair.\n< Erika >

It's a bit redder than mine... like wine
red... I wonder what kind of person she
was...\n< Erika >
Huh?\n< Erika >

An adventurer? I'm sure I put up the
'closed' sign... Really, at the worst
possible time.\n< Serena >

Could be the master too. Maybe he forgot
his keys or something.\n< Erika >
...Can't be helped...\n< Serena >
Yes, yes. Alright...\n< Erika >

No, Erika-sama, please stay seated. I'll
handle this.\n< Serena >

Though Serena's got her own troubles to
deal with...\n< Erika >
Oh... really? Sorry, that helps.\n< Erika >

Nothing serious...\n< Serena >

I'm so sorry... I've always been a bit

...\n< Serena >

回想セーブ ノーマルエンド
Cheers.\n< Serena >
Cheers.\n< Erika >
...\n< Serena >
...ahh.\n< Erika >

Kahahaha! So this is the sweet taste of
victory, huh?!\n< Erika >

I was rushed to the hospital after that
Minotaur incident and didn't even get a
sip of alcohol.\n< Erika >

To think we're celebrating that victory
now. You're as odd as ever.\n< Serena >

Serena, you've become quite the drinker
yourself. Did you learn to appreciate
the taste of alcohol in that town?\n< Erika >
Now, for another glass...\n< Erika >

Lady Erika, you are with child. You
shouldn't drink too much...\n< Serena >

Ah... right. Alcohol is bad for the kid
in my belly... wasn't it?\n< Erika >
That belly of yours...\n< Serena >

Well, I haven't slept with any other men
around that time. It must be one of
those guys' seed that hit the mark.\n< Erika >

I was too injured for an abortion.
Before I knew it, my belly had grown
this much.\n< Erika >

Now that it's come to this, there's
nothing to do but give birth. Even if
it's a child conceived from rape, I have
to give birth.\n< Erika >
But don't worry about me.\n< Erika >

More importantly, Serena, you've become
quite the drinker yourself. Did you
learn to appreciate the taste of alcohol
in that town?\n< Erika >

Well, I can't say I find it delicious.
But now, a little...\n< Serena >

No, actually, it still tastes strange.
It hits you right in the nose.\n< Serena >

Hahahaha! That's fine. If you start
guzzling it down from a young age,
you'll end up a lush like me.\n< Erika >

If I could become like Lady Erika,
perhaps I should try harder to enjoy
alcohol.\n< Serena >

Me? Oh no, I'm all battered and
nothing's going right for me. There's
nothing good about aiming to be like me.
Really, really...\n< Erika >

My body is just as battered. And look at
this belly...\n< Serena >
...\n< Erika >

My body is just as battered. What you
see on the outside is just this
bandage... but inside, it's
correspondingly...\n< Serena >

...which is why I am so astonished right
now.\n< Serena >

Your condition, your behavior, Lady
Erika. The magnitude of your strength...
how tremendous it is.\n< Serena >
Can I also behave like you from now on?\n< Serena >
...\n< Erika >
You found Splendor-chan, right?\n< Erika >

Yes, she was found. It was a bit of a
struggle though. While I'm here, Lady
Mary has been taking care of her.\n< Serena >

I managed to bring her from the eastern
town to here... but being with me now
seems to be quite a burden for
Splendor.\n< Serena >

Near Lady Mary's... daughter, Splendor
seems to find peace.\n< Serena >

It's this belly. When I showed my face,
I was cried upon... and shocked.\n< Serena >

...What do you plan to do from here on
out?\n< Erika >

Wait here for the pick-up from Gratia.
I've sent a letter, so they should be
arriving soon.\n< Serena >

But things have become serious... too
many things... have happened.\n< Serena >

Castellum is in an uproar right now. I
fled as if running away... what I did
there, what happened while I was there.\n< Serena >

Depending on how things go, it might
become an issue. At the very least, my
father will likely be implicated.\n< Serena >

Before the problem comes to light, if I
could just be admitted to some convent,
that would be the best possible
resolution.\n< Serena >

It will mean even more of a burden for
my sister, though.\n< Serena >
Are you really okay with that, Serena?\n< Erika >

Serena, you're betting your entire
future, sacrificing everything... and
the outcome is a life of confinement in
a convent?\n< Erika >

After all that effort to save Splendor-
chan, you won't ever be able to be close
with her again, right?\n< Erika >
...I can't accept that.\n< Erika >
Yes... I suppose...\n< Serena >

It's not necessarily the ending I wished
for.\n< Serena >
I am content... no...\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >

Hey, let's just run away now! Why not?
You're just going to be thrown into a
convent anyway, right?\n< Erika >

Then leave that damn troublesome house
behind! ...That's right! Let's become
adventurers together!\n< Erika >

Sure, there'll be plenty of hardships!
But it's freedom! The joy and the
sorrow, it's all yours!\n< Erika >

It might seem crazy with this belly and
these arms! But at least adventurers are
free! The joy and the sorrow, it's all
yours!\n< Erika >

Your life is your own, right!? Who do
you have to hold back for?\n< Erika >
...\n< Serena >

...Truly, you are so selfish and
imposing...\n< Serena >
And yet so considerate and sincere.\n< Serena >

From the first time you spoke to me
until now, you've always been concerned
about me.\n< Serena >

But it's impossible. I am a noble. An
executor of justice and responsibility.\n< Serena >

To save Splendor... I sacrificed many
things that were endowed to me.\n< Serena >

With each loss, I realized how
significant and heavy they were. Could
such great things really spring forth
from within me alone?\n< Serena >

...I thought about it. You were right,
Erika-dono. Just as Lady Mary had told
me.\n< Serena >

I was built upon the love and kindness
of my parents... no, even more people
than that.\n< Serena >

To shape who I am now, how much time and
effort must have been spent.\n< Serena >

How much love must have been poured into
me.\n< Serena >

And yet, I tarnished myself with my own
selfishness.\n< Serena >

The love that I should return to the
people I love... I've squandered it with
my own whims.\n< Serena >

I must accept the punishment. To flee
from responsibility, from sin... would
make me no different from the adults who
tormented me.\n< Serena >
That is something I cannot bear...\n< Serena >

Wait, Serena, that conclusion is wrong.
Why does it have to be like that?\n< Erika >

No one wants that for you... not like
that...\n< Erika >
It is what I want for myself.\n< Serena >

Seeing you, Erika-dono, made me realize
it once again.\n< Serena >

You surely did not run from your
responsibilities.\n< Serena >

The pain and hardship that resulted from
it. You bear it all without uttering a
single complaint to me.\n< Serena >

All that comes out of your mouth are
words of concern for me... I thought it
was amazing. That there could be someone
so strong.\n< Serena >

Now I bear a similar pain, and thus I
feel strongly. I want to be like you.\n< Serena >

No, you're wrong. That's not me... I
am...\n< Erika >

Thank you, Erika-dono. Because of you,
my heart is now clearer than ever
before.\n< Serena >

I'm going to write a letter.\n< Serena >

It might be filled with trivial things
like what I thought about each day or
what I read.\n< Serena >
But I would be happy if you read it.\n< Serena >

...I'm going to get some fresh air
outside.\n< Serena >

I may never come to this town again. I
want to take a good look and remember it
well.\n< Serena >
